Assignment No. 1
The reading task with answering questions about the materials read in the e-learning environment before the first seminars. The assessment follows the system of Fail/Pass. The general assessment criteria for independent work are the following:
* The paper has been submitted by the fixed deadline;
* Answers to the questions prepared are based on the materials read;
* Answers express analytical thinking skills;
* Language usage in the paper is correct;
* The sources used are referred to and listed in a correct manner.

Assignment No. 2
Giving an overview in a seminar of the case read. In a pair or group, initiating a discussion about the problematic issues, expressing opinions, and suggesting solutions in a seminar. The assessment follows the system of Fail/Pass. The general assessment criteria for pair or group work are the following:
* All group members have made themselves familiar with the materials;
* A brief overview of the case read is given in a seminar;
* 3-4 relevant discussion topics are opened up;
* All group members express their opinions and suggestions, being guided by the principles of patient-centered health care.

Assignment No. 4 (SUPPLEMENTARY TASK)
If a student is absent from the case analysis seminars, a reflection task from Moodle must be done as a supplementary task. It consists of submitting an essay summarizing all case analyses (5) (according to the general assessment criteria). The assessment follows the system of Fail/Pass. The general assessment criteria for independent work are the following:
* The written paper has been submitted by the fixed deadline (5 working days after the seminar in which the cases were analyzed);
* All the cases (5) have been briefly described and 5-6 relevant discussion topics have been raised from the cases, these have been analyzed from the bases of the principles of patient-centredness in health care;
* Language usage in the paper is correct;
* The sources used are referred to in a correct manner.
